		<div id="comment_body_64558793">If you can offer a good quality education at a lower price that will attract students, go right ahead....it's a free country and you can start a no-frills low-cost private institution.<br> <br>The fact is, students want clean, attractive facilities, they want the top professors, they want many food choices, and they want activities, clubs, sports, music, art...all of these things are expensive. Schools have tried to cut costs by not offering these things, but the students don't enroll.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64558793">

